  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Hi Jesica and anyone else,

I'm taking this for now. <a href="https://openhatch.org/wiki/Backups_of_the_live_site">https://openhatch.org/wiki/Backups_of_the_live_site</a> is
how things work as of the time of writing.

I see (from comments on this bug) that we are actually *not* successfully
backing up the bug tracker and wiki, nor blog.

Given that I flat-out forgot two important services in the backup plan, I think
I am going to switch from a backup structure that operates on whitelist basis,
and instead back up all of the root filesystem for the linode, with a handful of
small blacklisted directories that aren't essential to recovery (e.g.
/usr/share/doc/).

Do you have any other comments on the backup plan?</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
